('498af170-3760-47e7-9325-128f1ef5d947', 34, 217, 'https://images-wixmp-ed30a86b8c4ca887773594c2.wixmp.com/f/fe614050-2d22-43c4-a672-9af5709ffe11/dajpulz-39c6baba-20ad-4a46-b168-408b6e324a83.jpg?token=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9..cTK0eZFdtGp6cZXSTIF-oj3u916SbJuI-QFwtSXfJSQ', '▫️Short review: The Wailing (2016) is a chilling fusion of horror and folklore, immersing viewers in an atmosphere of paranoia and doubt. Na Hong-jin balances spiritual unease with visceral terror, leading to a hauntingly ambiguous finale that lingers long after the credits roll.', 'The Wailing (2016)', 'Folk Horror', 'Akyl_Lee/498af170-3760-47e7-9325-128f1ef5d947', 5.0, '2025-09-06 11:04:39', '2025-09-06 11:04:39'),
('49d95e2c-5447-4818-a489-ef8ea8661892', 52, 217, 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOWNmMzAzZmQtNDQ1NC00Nzk5LTkyMmUtNGI2N2NkOWM4MzEyXkEyXkFqcGc@._V1_FMjpg_UX1000_.jpg', 'A rare cinematic gem—bold, singular, and exhilarating. With its audacious storyline, the film elevates the multiverse concept to unprecedented heights beyond imagination. Profound themes of family, generational trauma, and existential crisis are rendered with striking clarity and nuance.\n▫️Rating • Plot: 10 • Twist: 7.5 • Acting: 10\n • Cine: 10 • Pacing: 8.8 • VFX: 9.0 • MU&H : 9.5  \n• Music: 8.9 ▫️Overall: 9.3 (⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️)', 'Everything Everywhere All at Once', 'Drama/Fantasy', 'Akyl_Lee/49d95e2c-5447-4818-a489-ef8ea8661892', 4.6, '2025-08-27 10:20:46', '2025-08-27 10:20:46'),
